          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "strong.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " Or rather, perhaps, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "he made the towers strong, i.e.,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " put them in a posture of defence. (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 11:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) The margin is wrong. Syriac, “girded (or bound) them at their corners with clamps (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "glîdê, i.e.,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
