        "class": "note_emph",
        "text": "(3)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that at the valley of Tyropoeon. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And at the turning",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "הַמִקְצוַע",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This word occurs eleven times, viz. twice in Exodus, four times in Nehemiah, four times in Ezekiel, and in this place, and is always rendered \"corner\" or\" turning;\" the word wanted is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "angle.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The site of this gate cannot very certainly be pronounced upon. Perhaps the angle that marks the gate is that at the south-east corner of the temple plateau. The language of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 3:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is our best clue: \"Next to him Ezer repaired...  a piece over against the going up to the armoury ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "at the turning.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " 2 Chronicles 26:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In order enduringly to establish the power of his kingdom, he still more strongly fortified Jerusalem by building towers at the gates, and the wall of the citadel. At the corner gate, i.e., at the north-west corner of the city (see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 25:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 14:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and at the valley gate, i.e., on the west side, where the Jaffa gate now is. From these sides Jerusalem was most open to attack. המּקצוע, at the corner, i.e., according to ",
        "children": []
